Heilbrunn Timeline of Art History: The United States and Canada, 1900 A.D.–present
Description: Trade cards from the "York Caramels" series (E210), issued 1927-28 to promote York Caramels for the York Caramel Company of York, Pennsylvania. The baseball cards were issued with two printed types of versos, one type printed in 1927 and the other in 1928. The museum set is affixed to the original album pages, so the versos are not visible and the verso types are unknown.
